<dl id="n08055j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08055j">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08055j"> 55(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> some blame the / &amp; more &mdash; the soot <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n08055j"><li>FW 119.33f </li><li><a href="../../flex/e/lexe.htm#n08055j">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/e/l39e.htm#n08055j">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n08055j">MS BL 47473-25</ms> </li><li>JJA 46:317 <a name="e4d2" href="../../ff/fdra/eda.htm#e4d2">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/e/ed2.htm#n08055j">Draft: I.5&sect;4.2</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">On pense aussit&ocirc;t &agrave; accuser la plume, mais contrai-rement aux apparences, elle est, dans ce cas, presque toujours innocente. Est-ce qu&apos;elle n&apos;a pas &eacute;t&eacute; choisie? Si elle ne l&apos;a pas &eacute;t&eacute; l&apos;&eacute;criture &eacute;paisse est accidentelle, donc n&eacute;gligeable. Si elle a &eacute;t&eacute; choisie le scripteur porte enti&egrave;rement la responsabilit&eacute; de ses trac&eacute;s &eacute;pais. Est-ce grossi&egrave;ret&eacute;? Quelquefois. Mais alors l&apos;&eacute;criture &eacute;pais se est associ&eacute;e &agrave; des formes vulgaires et inharmonieuses. <br>[One immediately thinks of accusing the pen, but contrary to the appearances, it is, in this case, almost always innocent. Has not she been chosen? If it has not been written thick is accidental, so negligible. If chosen, the writer is entirely responsible for his thick lines. Is it rudeness? Sometimes. But then thick writing is associated with vulgar and unharmonious forms. <small> J Cr&eacute;pieux-Jamin, <a name="JCJL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JCJL"><cite title="source">Les &eacute;l&eacute;ments de l'&eacute;criture des canailles</cite></a> (1923) 224</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also: <a name="sa0721ax" href="saall.htm#sa0721ax">SA (VI.A):0721(ax)</a> </mm> </dd></dl>
